  "riddle": "1. A vibrant culture thrives in the northern heart of England. In what year did a writer pen ‘God’s Own Country’ for a special edition of a prestigious lifestyle magazine that pays homage to this land?\n\n2. Seek the page where the unique manner of speaking reveals itself through various regions — how many audio examples showcase the local way with words?\n\n3. Elevated amidst the hills, what is the height recorded for the local dialect that colors conversations in this region?\n\n4. Among nature's breathing spaces, how many parks can one find within reach of the unique tongue spoken here?\n\n5. Combine the height you have discovered in clue 3 with the number of parks from clue 4. What new value emerges from this addition?\n\n6. What year does the image of a certain woollen headwear, sported by an acclaimed actor, indicate in its caption?\n\n7. A legendary stretch of land awaits: can you compute the total number of days from the dawn of 2005 to the crisp spring day of 2026?\n\n8. When reflecting on the answer obtained from clue 7, what number do you unveil by reversing its digits?\n\n9. Drive through history: what is the distance in miles between the ancient city once known as Eboracum and the loud voice of the local dialect?\n\n10. Once again, measure the passage of time: confirm how many days span from the start of 2005 to the arrival of spring in 2026.\n\n11. Looking towards the next celestial number, what is the prime that follows the figure you derived from clue 10?\n\n12. Finally, determine the outcome of taking the absolute difference between your findings from clue 8 and clue 9, then reduce it through modulus 10. What single digit does this computation yield?",
